<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-15495] DefaultVertxHttpBinding ignores exchange content-type request header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-15495</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I made a mistake in the DefaultVertxHttpBinding implementation in that if the content-type exchange header is set, it gets stripped by the HeaderFilterStrategy, and is never set on the Vert.x HttpRequest object.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The workaround until a fix is available would be to extend DefaultVertxHttpBinding and override populateRequestHeaders so that content-type can be set properly.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
